Tabocalypse agent rules (for Cline and similar tools)

Source of truth:
- AGENTS.md (behavior)
- .cursor/rules/project-conventions.mdc (repo + product constraints)
- .cursor/rules/*.mdc with alwaysApply: true (additional Cursor rules)
- doc/AGENT-INSTRUCTIONS.md (agent-agnostic rule index; keep this file aligned)

Hard constraints:
- pnpm only (no npm)
- extension UI: Tailwind only
- TypeScript: no `any`
- naming: interfaces I*, type aliases T*
- filenames: kebab-case
- product: no publisher backend/keys; declarative plugins only (no user JS execution)
- never paste secrets (.env, tokens, API keys, user data)

Workflow:
- prefer small, surgical diffs; avoid whole-file rewrites
- ask for patch-shaped output per file
- verify before done: pnpm run check; and pnpm run build when extension UI/packaging/tooling is touched

